@node Cap01 "Introduction"
  =======================================================================
  5D-BaudCheck is a tool which allows the sysop to don't allow users with
  low baud connect to enter into the bbs except some users who have the
  password to enter.
  =======================================================================
@endnode
@node Cap02 "Requirements"
  =======================================================================
  To install 5D-BaudCheck you must have the following things:

    Programm      Location            Description
    ----------    --------            -----------
    5D-BaudCheck  Doors:5D-BaudCheck  Main program

  - an  Amiga Model (500/600/1000/1200/2000/2500/3000/4000/CDTV/CDł˛)
  - the installed Version of OS\2, OS\3, OS/432 or higher
    (Soft-, Bit-, Hardware Version)
  - the installed .INFO Files in the directories.
  - AmiExpress V2.xx , v3.xx , v4.xx or higher.

  =======================================================================
@endnode
@node Cap03 "How to install 5D-BaudCheck"
  =======================================================================
  To install 5D-BaudCheck you must have all Requirement which were
  mentioned below. You need the following things.

  --------------------------
    Doors:5D-BaudCheck (dir)
      ^^^ 5D-BaudCheck
    BBS:Commands/SysCmd (dir)
      ^^^ FRONTEND.info
  --------------------------

  Decruch the 5D-BaudCheck Archive. Go to your 'Doors:' Directory
  and make a Directory called '5D-BaudCheck'. Copy '5D-BaudCheck'
  into the Directory. Go to your 'BBS:Commands/SysCmd' Directory.
  Copy 'FRONTEND.info' into it.
  =======================================================================
@endnode
@node Cap04 "Tooltype Informations..."
  =======================================================================
  - All tooltypes available in 'Doors:5D-BaudCheck/5D-BaudCheck.info'

  LOW_BAUD=2400               - Allows you to set the baud rate at which
                                5D-BaudCheck shall ask the user for the
                                password. If he enters the wrong pw he
                                will be logged out!
  PASSWORD=LAMER_SUX          - Allows you to set the pw which will
                                be asked if the baud rate is not high
                                enough.
  =======================================================================
@endnode
